Lead design on Umbra's internal C3 application, Omniscience, built in React. This application is the hub for all satellite operations within Umbra including managing/creating tasks, mission planning, and ephemeris management.

## Umbra Space Platform

The Umbra Space Platform provides users with access to high-resolution satellite imagery and powerful analysis tools. The platform enables users to search, filter, and analyze satellite data with an intuitive interface.

### Key Features

- Advanced search and filtering capabilities
- Interactive map visualization
- Data analysis tools
- User-friendly interface
- Real-time satellite tracking

The platform was designed with a focus on usability, ensuring that complex geospatial data is accessible to users with varying levels of expertise.

Exploring the land of fire and ice, from the Northern Lights to geothermal hot springs and dramatic waterfalls.

Iceland was absolutely breathtaking! The landscapes were so diverse and dramatic. From the powerful Gullfoss waterfall to the ethereal Northern Lights dancing across the sky, every moment was magical.

## Highlights

- **Northern Lights**: Witnessed an incredible aurora display over the Jökulsárlón glacier lagoon
- **Geysir**: Watched the famous Strokkur geyser erupt every few minutes
- **Blue Lagoon**: Relaxed in the milky blue geothermal waters
- **Ring Road**: Drove the complete circle around the island

The midnight sun in summer and the cozy winter nights made this trip unforgettable. Iceland truly is a photographer's paradise!

Diving into the vibrant culture of Tokyo, from bustling street markets to serene temples and cutting-edge technology.

Tokyo was an incredible sensory overload in the best possible way! The city seamlessly blends ancient traditions with ultra-modern innovation.

## Unforgettable Experiences

- **Shibuya Crossing**: Standing in the middle of the world's busiest pedestrian crossing
- **Senso-ji Temple**: Finding peace in the ancient temple grounds of Asakusa
- **Tsukiji Market**: Sampling the freshest sushi and experiencing the tuna auctions
- **Harajuku**: Immersing myself in the colorful youth culture and fashion scene
- **Golden Gai**: Discovering tiny bars in the narrow alleys of Shinjuku

The combination of incredible food, friendly people, and unique experiences made Tokyo one of my favorite destinations. Can't wait to return!
